  "response": "As of 2023, there are several smartphones under \u20b912,000 that offer great value for money with decent performance, good cameras, and long battery life. Here are some of the best options:\n\n### 1. **Realme Narzo 50i Prime**\n   - **Price**: \u20b97,999\n   - **Display**: 6.5-inch HD+ LCD\n   - **Processor**: Unisoc T612\n   - **RAM/Storage**: 3GB/32GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera**: 8MP rear, 5MP front\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh\n   - **OS**: Android 11 (Go Edition)\n\n### 2. **Redmi 11 Prime 5G (Base Variant)**\n   - **Price**: \u20b911,999\n   - **Display**: 6.58-inch Full HD+ 90Hz LCD\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Dimensity 700\n   - **RAM/Storage**: 4GB/64GB\n   - **Camera**: 50MP dual rear, 5MP front\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh, 18W fast charging\n   - **OS**: MIUI 13 (Android 12)\n\n### 3. **Samsung Galaxy M04**\n   - **Price**: \u20b98,999\n   - **Display**: 6.5-inch HD+ PLS LCD\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio P35\n   - **RAM/Storage**: 4GB/64GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera**: 13MP dual rear, 5MP front\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh\n   - **OS**: Android 12\n\n### 4. **POCO C55**\n   - **Price**: \u20b98,999\n   - **Display**: 6.71-inch HD+ IPS LCD\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio G85\n   - **RAM/Storage**: 4GB/64GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera**: 50MP dual rear, 5MP front\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh, 10W charging\n   - **OS**: MIUI 13 (Android 12)\n\n### 5. **Infinix Smart 7**\n   - **Price**: \u20b97,499\n   - **Display**: 6.6-inch HD+ IPS LCD\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio G25\n   - **RAM/Storage**: 3GB/32GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera**: 13MP rear, 5MP front\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh, 10W charging\n   - **OS**: Android 12 (Go Edition)\n\n### 6. **Lava Blaze 2**\n   - **Price**: \u20b99,499\n   - **Display**: 6.5-inch HD+ IPS LCD\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio G37\n   - **RAM/Storage**: 4GB/64GB (expandable)\n   - **Camera**: 13MP dual rear, 8MP front\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh, 10W charging\n   - **OS**: Android 12\n\n### Key Considerations:\n- **Performance**: Look for MediaTek Helio G series or Unisoc T612 processors for smooth performance.\n- **Display**: HD+ resolution is standard in this range; some phones offer 90Hz refresh rates.\n- **Battery**: Most phones in this range come with 5000mAh batteries, ensuring good battery life.\n- **Camera**: Entry-level smartphones usually have 13MP or 50MP primary cameras, which are decent for casual photography.\n- **Software**: Android 12 or newer is preferable for better features and security.\n\nThese smartphones are excellent for budget-conscious buyers seeking a balance between performance and price. Always check current prices and offers as they can change frequently.",
